※※
# audit-sky-secrets

Manually-run workflow that scans every `.sky` in a directory for **secret-shaped**
environment-variable references inside `bash`/`http` lines that are NOT declared in
that workflow's `secrets = [...]` array, and reports the undeclared ones. Pure bash,
no LLM tokens. Exits non-zero if any undeclared secret-shaped reference is found.

Why secret-shaped: a `.sky` bash node is full of ordinary shell locals (`f`, `tmp`,
`N`). Flagging all of them is noise. This targets the real risk — names that look like
credentials — and leaves plain locals alone.

A name is "secret-shaped" if it contains an underscore (e.g. `DATABASE_URL`,
`GITHUB_TOKEN`) OR matches `token|secret|password|passwd|apikey|credential`
(case-insensitive). `$SKY_*` template vars are always exempt.

  (manual run: --var dir)
       │
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  per file: secret-shaped env refs in bash/http  ▶  minus secrets[]
   │  scan  │  exit 1 if any file has an undeclared one
   └────────┘

Heuristic, not a parser — treat output as "review these". Silence a real one by
declaring it in `secrets = [...]`.

Run it (state which directory to scan with --var dir):

  sky run audit-sky-secrets --var dir=".sky/workflows"

  - dir   directory of .sky files to scan — STATE THIS (e.g. .sky/workflows)
※※

⊕meta⊕
name = "audit-sky-secrets"
description = "Scan every .sky for secret-shaped $ENV refs in bash/http not declared in secrets[], report the undeclared ones, exit non-zero on any. Pure bash. Fire via: sky run audit-sky-secrets --var dir=<path>"
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
⊕⊕

※※
Step 1 — scan. The whole audit in one bash pass. For each file: collect names declared
in any secrets = [ ... ] array, collect env tokens used on bash/http lines (dropping
$SKY_* template vars), keep only the secret-shaped ones, and report any not declared.
Env tokens are matched with a [$] character class so this scanner never trips
SKY-WF-055 on itself.
※※

§scan§
bash = "set -e\nif [ ! -d \"$SKY_DIR\" ]; then echo \"[secrets] no such dir: $SKY_DIR\"; exit 1; fi\nrc=0\nfor f in \"$SKY_DIR\"/*.sky; do\n  [ -e \"$f\" ] || continue\n  declared=$(grep -oE 'secrets[[:space:]]*=[[:space:]]*\\[[^]]*\\]' \"$f\" | grep -oE '\"[A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_]*\"' | tr -d '\"' | sort -u)\n  used=$(grep -E '^(bash|http)' \"$f\" | grep -oE '[$][{]?[A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_]*' | tr -d '${' | sort -u | grep -vE '^SKY_' || true)\n  flagged=\"\"\n  for u in $used; do\n    printf '%s' \"$u\" | grep -qE '_' || printf '%s' \"$u\" | grep -qiE 'token|secret|password|passwd|apikey|credential' || continue\n    printf '%s\\n' \"$declared\" | grep -qx \"$u\" && continue\n    flagged=\"$flagged $u\"\n  done\n  if [ -n \"$flagged\" ]; then echo \"FAIL  $(basename \"$f\"):$flagged\"; rc=1; fi\ndone\nif [ \"$rc\" -eq 0 ]; then echo \"[secrets] no undeclared secret-shaped env reads found\"; else echo \"[secrets] undeclared secret-shaped env refs — declare real ones in secrets = [...]\"; fi\nexit \"$rc\""
§§
